    ∇ CACHEINIT;∆set;T;P;C;head;cachepath;Q;I[1]   ⍝Initialize grid cache on local machine[2]   ⍝This function expects c:\cache_config.txt to exist.  It should include:[3]   ⍝   cachepath   path to machine's grid cache[4]   ⍝   maxsize     maximum size of cache, in GB[5]   ⍝   minfree     minimum amount of free space left on disk in GB[6]   ⍝   nbins       number of bins used when hashing the grid path to identify index file[7]   ⍝   deletesize  amount of space to clear up at a time, in GB[8]   ⍝*** Warning! Clears entire cache--use with care![9]   ⍝B. Compton, 6 Sep 2013[10]  ⍝16 May 2016: Revised for new hashed cache scheme[11]  ⍝19 May 2016: drop gridinfo columns--we don't use them[12]  [13]  [14]  [15]   :if ~IFEXISTS C←'c:\cache_config.txt'[16]      ⎕←'Caching is turned off for this machine because ',C,' doesn''t exist.'[17]   :else[18]      GETCACHECONFIG[19]      RMDIR P←2⊃cache                         ⍝Nuke old gridcache directory if it exists[20]      MAKEDIR P                               ⍝(Re)create it[21]      MAKEDIR Q←P,'index\'                    ⍝Create index path [22]      (2 1⍴'0') MATOUT Q,'cacheinfo.txt'      ⍝Create cacheinfo file[23]  [24]      head←1↓⎕TCHT MTOV MATRIFY 'source cache status cachedate sourcedate reads size'  ⍝Dropped columns: cols rows xll yll cellsize nodata type min max mean std[25]      I←0[26]  L1: →(cache[5]<I←I+1)/L2                    ⍝For each cache index,[27]      '' TMATOUT Q,(⍕I),'.txt'                ⍝   Create cache index[28]      →L1[29]      [30]  L2:  ⎕←'Grid cache created in ',P[31]   :end     ∇